actions.message:
`In order for the bot to Welcome users and give them a Guest role

1. Creat A Guest role
2. Create a Welcome channel - for the welcomes to be seen

I put it on a serch value for this channel
I also did this for Guest on a searched role.

!welcomeon and !welcomeoff to turn it on or off

The bot has to be higher rank then the guest role.
It must also have access to give ranks. 

It also has to be able to see and talk in the Welcome channel

!announce - also needs an announcements channel.

Both "announcements" and "welcome" need to be spelled exactly
they must also have nothing before or after just whats in " "s

A "bot-log" channel will show any errors with the bot and admin
type stuff. Users Joined and Left ect. I plan to expand this.`

actions.message:
In-Game Description: Nightblades are adventurers and opportunists with a gift for getting in and out of trouble. Relying variously on stealth, blades, and speed.

**Assassination**
The Assassination skill is orientated towards melee attackers, particularly dual-wielding, with abilities ranging from increasing your attack speed to teleporting to your target and damaging them at the same time.

**Shadow**
The Shadow skill is orientated towards self-preservation, with abilities ranging from inflicting fear on nearby enemies to becoming invisible and some crowd-control.

**Siphoning**
The Siphoning skill is oriented towards spell-casting assassins, with abilities that de-buff and damage enemies and provide healing and positive buffs to you. These abilities range from decreasing nearby enemies' attack power to casting a damage-over-time spell on a target that casts a healing spell on you for the same duration.
actions.name: Add Embed Field

actions.message:
Sorcerer is the class with the most magical abilities. In-Game Description: Sorcerers can use conjuration and destruction spells to hurl lightning bolts and create shock fields, wield dark magic to snare and stun, and summon Daedric combat followers from Oblivion to assist them.

**Dark Magic**
Dark Magic is one of three class skill lines available to Sorcerer characters. Skills in this line focus on stuns and utility spells and are good for a supporting role.

**Daedric Summoning**
Daedric Summoning is one of three class skill lines available to Sorcerer characters. This is very similar to Conjuration in that you summon Daedric creatures, such as atronachs and familiars.

**Storm Calling**
Storm Calling is one of three class skill lines available to Sorcerer characters. Skills in this line focus on magical DPS (damage per second) and burst damage, mostly themed towards lightning magic.

actions.message:
Warden is a class in Elder Scrolls Online. It was originally only available to players who have purchased the Morrowind Chapter, but is now available as a Crown Store Upgrade for 1500 Crowns instead. It is not included in the Morrowind DLC currently available for purchase. Warden is a nature-themed class, with a focus on frost magic and animal companions.

In-Game Description: Wardens are defenders of the Green, master storytellers whose nature tales become magical reality. They wield frost spells against enemies and summon animals to aid them.

**Animal Companions**
Green Balance is geared towards healing and buffs.

**Green Balance**
Dawn's Wrath represents the power of the sun, using light and fire to damage enemies directly, assist allies with their damage, or reflecting enemy damage.

**Winter's Embrace**
Winter's Embrace is geared towards dealing Frost Damage and tanking.

actions.message:
Dragonknight is a class in Elder Scrolls Online. It is geared primarily towards tanking characters, but also utilizing fire to deal magic damage.

In-Game Description: These skillful masters-at-arms use the ancient Akaviri martial arts tradition of battle-spirit, and wield fearsome magic that pounds, shatters and physically alters the world around them.

**Ardent Flame**
Ardent Flame is geared towards fire damage.

**Draconic Power**
Draconic Power is geared mainly towards self-preservation and tanking.

**Earthen Heart**
Earthen Heart is a mix of self-defense and support abilities.

actions.message:
Templar is a class in Elder Scrolls Online. Its skill lines represent the teachings of Stendarr, wielding light and fire to smite the wicked, or to heal and support the wounded.

In-Game Description: These traveling knights call upon the powers of light and the burning sun to deal massive damage to their enemies while restoring health, magicka, and stamina to their allies.

**Aedric Spear**
Aedric Spear uses the power of light to deal damage at any range and protect the caster with a powerful shield.

**Dawn's Wrath**
Dawn's Wrath represents the power of the sun, using light and fire to damage enemies directly, assist allies with their damage, or reflecting enemy damage.

**Restoring Light**
Restoring Light is focused towards magical support and strong healing abilities.

actions.message: When word reached the High Elves of Alinor that the Imperial City had fallen under the control of the human supporters of Molag Bal, the Aldmeri Dominion was formed. The High Elves reached out to the neighboring races of Wood Elves and Khajiit with a plea that their combined forces might prevent the younger races of Tamriel from bringing disaster to the world, as they had so many times in the past. The High Elves were the original settlers of Tamriel and created the common tongue used throughout the continent today. They are also naturally proficient with magic. The Wood Elves inhabit the thick, near-impenetrable forests of Valenwood. They are supreme hunters, guides, and masters in sneaking and thievery. They are also the most gifted archers in all of Tamriel. The Khajiit, a proud feline race, are fearsome warriors, proficient with bladed weapons.

actions.message:
The Daggerfall Covenant is a compact between the peoples of northwest Tamriel—Bretons, Redguards, and Orcs—that forms an alliance of mutual defense, with a vision of establishing peace and order across Tamriel. Indeed, the kings of the Covenant take the Remans as their model.

So this is the modern Daggerfall Covenant, an alliance of the Redguards of northern Hammerfell, under King Fahara'jad; the Orcs of the mountainous northeast, under King Kurog of Orsinium; with the Breton King Emeric of High Rock presiding from his palace in Wayrest. At its best, it is a noble alliance of honorable and chivalrous peoples, representing all the best aspects of the First and Second Empires. And from this solid foundation, perhaps a third, even mightier Empire shall arise, providing all the peoples of Tamriel the benefits of mutual respect, vigorous trade, and reverence for the Divines.
